                  </hi> I was assistant to John Thomas Neal, pawnbroker, of Duke-street, Manchester-square—I produce a case of instruments—I cannot say who pledged them—I gave duplicate, which has been produced.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471025-name-428" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-428" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-428" type="surname" value="AUSTEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-428" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD AUSTEN.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a student at the College—this case of instru<lb></lb>ments is mine, and was in my desk, in the lecture-room, before it was lost.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> The things were placed in my box without my know<lb></lb>ledge; it is impossible for any person to get into the College from outside—the window is bound in the middle with an iron bar, and is not above three or four inches wide.</p>
